# Adapter trimming and quality filtering of FASTQ files
Trim Galore (v0.6.7)
Citation: Babraham Bioinformatics

# Alignment to the mouse genome (GRCm38/mm10)
Bowtie2 (v2.4.2)
Citation: Langmead & Salzberg, Nat Methods, 2012

# Sorting and deduplication of BAM files
SAMtools (v1.13)
Citation: Li et al., Bioinformatics, 2009

# Peak calling (H3K9ac, H3K14ac, H3K9bhb)
MACS2 (v2.2.9.1)	
Citation: Zhang et al., Genome Biol, 2008

# Intersecting and comparing genomic intervals
BEDtools (v2.3.0)	
Citation: Quinlan & Hall, Bioinformatics, 2010

# Peak annotation and motif analysis
HOMER (v4.1)
Citation: http://homer.ucsd.edu/homer/

# Signal processing, normalization, heatmap visualization
DeepTools (v3.3.1)
• bamCoverage	–	Generate BigWig files from BAM	
• bamCompare	–	Log₂ fold change comparison	
• computeMatrix	–	Compute score matrices for visualization	
• plotHeatmap	–	Plot heatmaps	
Citation: Ramírez et al., Nucleic Acids Res, 2016

# Genome browser for visualization
Integrative Genomics Viewer	(IGV, v2.17)	
Citation: Robinson et al., Nat Biotechnol, 2011
